# Git Workflow

After every meaningful change (new feature, bug fix, milestone completion):

1. Stage all relevant files with `git add`
2. Write a concise commit message describing the change
3. Run `git push` to keep the remote up to date

This project deploys via GitHub Pages, so pushing to `main` should always leave the build in a deployable state. Never push broken or half-finished code -- complete the current unit of work first, then commit and push.
